'''''A Queen's Ransom''''', also known as '''''International Assassin''''', is a 1976 [[Hong Kong action cinema|Hong Kong action film]] about a plot to assassinate [[Queen Elizabeth II]]. The film was written and directed by [[Ting Shan-hsi]] and starred [[Jimmy Wang Yu]], [[Angela Mao]], [[George Lazenby]], [[Ko Chun-hsiung]], [[Charles Heung]] and [[Dean Shek]], whom also serves as the film's assistant director.

==Plot==
During Queen Elizabeth II's visit to Hong Kong in 1975, a group of criminals plan her assassination.

